article_title: HealthCare.gov Expected to Work Better This Year, but Some States Struggle
article_text:
HealthCare.gov is expected to work better, but a handful of state-run insurance exchanges face problems going into the second year of sign-ups for health plans, starting on Saturday, under the Affordable Care Act.

Obama administration officials say the federal enrollment site will be simpler, faster and more intuitive than last year, when crashes and bottlenecks frustrated shoppers. In many states, consumers will have more insurance...
